---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, viewport-fit=cover" />
    <title>Privacy Policy | VTracer WASM</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for VTracer WASM. Learn what data we (do not) collect and how the app works entirely in your browser." />
    <meta name="color-scheme" content="dark" />
  </head>
  <body class="min-h-screen bg-black text-gray-100">
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 space-y-8">
      <header class="space-y-2">
        <p class="text-sm text-emerald-400 uppercase tracking-wide">VTracer WASM</p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-400">
          Effective Date: December 8, 2025
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="space-y-3 text-gray-200 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          VTracer WASM is a 100% client-side image to SVG converter. All vectorization happens directly in your
          browser using WebAssembly. We do not collect, store, or transmit your images or any personal data to our servers.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
          <li><strong>No uploads.</strong> Images are processed locally in your browser.</li>
          <li><strong>No tracking.</strong> We do not use cookies, analytics, or third-party trackers.</li>
          <li><strong>No accounts.</strong> We do not require login or store user profiles.</li>
          <li><strong>Network requests.</strong> The only network calls are to load the site assets and check for service worker updates.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If you open the app from <a class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline" href="https://jarettrude.github.io/vtracer-wasm/">https://jarettrude.github.io/vtracer-wasm/</a>,
          all processing remains on your device. If you self-host, ensure you serve the site over HTTPS to retain the same privacy guarantees.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 text-gray-200 leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-300">Local Storage</h2>
        <p>
          We do not persist your images. The app may store small preferences (e.g., selected options) in your browser's local storage to improve
          your experience, but these never leave your device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 text-gray-200 leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-300">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          The app does not embed third-party analytics, advertising, or social widgets.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you follow links to third-party sites (docs, source, or other resources), their content and data practices are governed by their own
          privacy policies and terms. Review those before using their services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 text-gray-200 leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-300">Questions</h2>
        <p>
          Have a question or found an issue? Open an issue on GitHub:
          <a class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline" href="https://github.com/jarettrude/vtracer-wasm">https://github.com/jarettrude/vtracer-wasm</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <footer class="pt-6 border-t border-emerald-800 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
          <a href="/vtracer-wasm/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline">Back to App</a>
          <span class="text-gray-600">|</span>
          <a href="/vtracer-wasm/terms-of-service" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline">Terms of Service</a>
          <span class="text-gray-600">|</span>
          <a href="https://github.com/jarettrude/vtracer-wasm" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline">GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
